⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Dunya Raskolnikova
node CRP · CRP · ⟦Dunya Raskolnikova:CRP:438d7f⟧

WHO   — Dunya Raskolnikova — the sister · the unbought
WHAT  — The counter-example of strength with conscience: she will sell herself in marriage to help her brother but will not sell her soul, and faces down Svidrigailov with a pistol.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel needs a will as strong as Raskolnikov's that does <i>not</i> break the moral law — proof the theory was never necessary.
HOW   — By integrity, courage, and a refusal of both Luzhin's contempt and Svidrigailov's coercion.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  My brother thought strength meant standing above the law; I was as strong as he, and I never once stepped over it.

